Reference - Authors: Gregg A Dean; Alora LaVoy; Mary Jo Burkhard
Reference - Title: Peptide mapping of feline immunodeficiency virus by IFN-gamma ELISPOT.
Epitope - Epitope Comments: The cats in this study were infected with the FIV molecular clone NCSU1.
1st immunogen - Name: Feline immunodeficiency virus (feline immunodeficiency virus FIV)
Immunization - Comments: Eight cats infected by intravenous route with the Feline Immunodeficiency Virus molecular clone NCSU1 for 1-2 years.
Assay - Comments: This assay was performed in lymph node mononuclear cells which were either CD8+ or CD4+ depleted. Reactivity to this epitope was completely abrogated in the CD8+ depleted cultures, indicating this epitope is CD8+ restricted.The lymph node mononuclear cells used in the assay were from a single cat that was found to have broad reactivity to the individual peptides selected for the gene-specific pools.  The other 7 subjects were not evaluated.

Reference - Title: Peptide mapping of feline immunodeficiency virus by IFN-gamma ELISPOT.
Epitope - Epitope Comments: The cats in this study were infected with the FIV molecular clone NCSU1.

Reference - Authors: L Mortara; H Gras-Masse; C Rommens; A Venet; J G Guillet; I Bourgault-Villada
Reference - Title: Type 1 CD4(+) T-cell help is required for induction of antipeptide multispecific cytotoxic T lymphocytes by a lipopeptidic vaccine in rhesus macaques.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: Three injections with 500 µg of each lipopeptides s.c. at 1-month intervals.
Immunization - Comments: Monkeys were immunized with 500 µg of tetanus toxoid in IFA (3 s.c. and one i.m.) at one month intervals. Seven months later, animals were given three additional injections s.c. of a mixture of lipopeptide micelle (500 µg of each) at 1-month intervals.  PBMC from immunized animals were cultured with a mixture of 10 µM of each free long peptides for 3 days followed by addition of IL-2. CTL were restimulated with peptide-pulsed irradiated autologous PBMC weekly.
Assay - Comments: CTL lines were derived from monkeys immunized with tetanus toxoid and mixture of long lipopeptides which the C-terminus were palmitoylated with Nε-palmitoyl-lysylamide. Specific killing was measured against free long peptides and overlapping short peptides (8-11 aa) to identify the epitope.

Reference - Authors: Tara L Tagmyer; Jodi K Craigo; Sheila J Cook; Charles J Issel; Ronald C Montelaro
Reference - Title: Envelope-specific T-helper and cytotoxic T-lymphocyte responses associated with protective immunity to equine infectious anemia virus.
Immunization - Comments: Twelve horses were vaccinated with live-attenuated EIAV (D9), which contains an engineered 9 base pair deletion and 2 termination codons in the viral S2 gene. Each vaccinated horse seroconverted by 35 days post-inoculation and responses were confirmed at 6 months post-vaccination. Horses were vaccinated twice at 30-day intervals by injection of 105 50% tissue culture infective dose (TCID50) of the vaccine stock.
Assay - Comments: PBMCs from 12 vaccinated horses were tested for proliferation in response to the epitope.  All 12 horses were protected from virulent virus challenge, as evidenced by lack of clinical signs and undetectable virus in plasma.
MHC Restriction - Evidence Code: T cell assay -T cell subset identification

Each vaccinated horse seroconverted by 35 days post-inoculation and responses were confirmed at 6 months post-vaccination. Horses were vaccinated twice at 30-day intervals by injection of 105 50% tissue culture infective dose (TCID50) of the vaccine stock.
Assay - Comments: PBMCs from 12 vaccinated horses were tested for proliferation in response to the epitope. No response was observed to this peptide.
MHC Restriction - Evidence Code: T cell assay -T cell subset identification

Reference - Title: Envelope-specific T-helper and cytotoxic T-lymphocyte responses associated with protective immunity to equine infectious anemia virus.
Immunization - Comments: Twelve horses were vaccinated with live-attenuated EIAV (D9), which contains an engineered 9 base pair deletion and 2 termination codons in the viral S2 gene. Each vaccinated horse seroconverted by 35 days post-inoculation and responses were confirmed at 6 months post-vaccination. Horses were vaccinated twice at 30-day intervals by injection of 105 50% tissue culture infective dose (TCID50) of the vaccine stock.
Assay - Comments: PBMCs from 12 vaccinated horses were tested for proliferation in response to the epitope. No response was observed to this peptide.
MHC Restriction - Evidence Code: T cell assay -T cell subset identification

Reference - Title: Envelope-specific T-helper and cytotoxic T-lymphocyte responses associated with protective immunity to equine infectious anemia virus.
in vitro immunogen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)
Immunization - Comments: Twelve horses were vaccinated with live-attenuated EIAV (D9), which contains an engineered 9 base pair deletion and 2 termination codons in the viral S2 gene. in vitro immunogen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)
Immunization - Comments: Twelve horses were vaccinated with live-attenuated EIAV (D9), which contains an engineered 9 base pair deletion and 2 termination codons in the viral S2 gene. Each vaccinated horse seroconverted by 35 days post-inoculation and responses were confirmed at 6 months post-vaccination. Horses were vaccinated twice at 30-day intervals by injection of 105 50% tissue culture infective dose (TCID50) of the vaccine stock. PBMCs were expanded in vitro for 7-10 days with purified EIAV (10ug/ml) prior to CTL assay.
Assay - Comments: PBMCs from 12 vaccinated horses were tested for cytolysis against peptide-pulsed targets.

Immunization - Comments: Twelve horses were vaccinated with live-attenuated EIAV (D9), which contains an engineered 9 base pair deletion and 2 termination codons in the viral S2 gene. Assay - Comments: PBMCs from 12 vaccinated horses were tested for proliferation in response to the epitope.  This peptide elicited both CD4 and CD8 proliferation. All 12 horses were protected from virulent virus challenge, as evidenced by lack of clinical signs and undetectable virus in plasma.
MHC Restriction - Evidence Code: T cell assay -T cell subset identification

Reference - Title: Epitope specificity is critical for high and moderate avidity cytotoxic T lymphocytes associated with control of viral load and clinical disease in horses with equine infectious anemia virus.
Epitope - Epitope Comments: This epitope is from a variant isolated from a horse infected with strain WSU5 that developed progressive EIAV. Only a small portion of the envelope protein was sequenced and submitted to the database, so the amino acid sequences from the fragment differ from the envelope protein described in the paper.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 1 dose of 107 50% tissue culture infective doses
Immunization - Comments: PBMC were incubated with 40 μM peptide for 2 hours, after which excess peptide was removed and cells were cultured for seven days prior to use.

Reference - Authors: Darrilyn G Fraser; Steve R Leib; Bao Shan Zhang; Robert H Mealey; Wendy C Brown; Travis C McGuire
Reference - Title: Lymphocyte proliferation responses induced to broadly reactive Th peptides did not protect against equine infectious anemia virus challenge.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 5 doses of 8.9 mg, administered at intervals of 2 weeks.
Immunization - Comments: Horses were immunized with a mixture of lipopeptides derived from proteins of equine infectious anemia virus. The peptides were: gag 221-245 (QGPIPMTARFIRGLGVPRERQMEPA), gag 250-269 (RQTYRQWIIEAMSEGIKVMI), gag 13-32 (KLEKVTVQGSQKLTTGNCNW), pol 326-347(LPQGFVLSPYIYQKTLQEILQP), pol 704-719 (EIVYFAWVPGHKGIYG), env 195-206 (RVEDVMNTTEYW), and pol704-env195 (EIVYFAWVPGHKGIYGPGPGRVEDVMNTTEYWRVEDVMNTTEYW). The first dose was in CFA, while booster doses were in IFA. Two weeks later, immunized horses were challenged intravenously with pathogenic pony-virulent strain of equine infectious anemia virus. PBMCs were obtained one week after the last booster dose, and 1 and 3 weeks after virus challenge. The carrier was composed of Palmitic Acid.
Assay - Comments: Highest number of responders was observed 1 week after viral challenge. Positive response was also observed in most horses one week after completion of the immunization.

Immunization - Comments: PBMC from each infected horse were stimulated with a pool of 15-16 amino acid peptides containing this peptide.
Assay - Comments: The functional avidity of CTL recognition of this peptide was low: > 1000 nm. Not all carrier horses had high functional avidity CTL to Gag EC, but those that did had longer periods without disease episodes.

Reference - Authors: Chungwon Chung; Robert H Mealey; Travis C McGuire
Reference - Title: Evaluation of high functional avidity CTL to Gag epitope clusters in EIAV carrier horses.
1st immunogen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)
Immunization - Comments: PBMC from each infected horse were stimulated with a pool of 15-16 amino acid peptides containing this peptide.
Assay - Comments: The functional avidity of CTL recognition of this peptide was low: > 1000 nm. Not all carrier horses had high functional avidity CTL to Gag EC, but those that did had longer periods without disease episodes. Synthetic peptides generated to represent the sequence of EIAV variants were used to show that the R to K change at position 4 resulted in CTL escape from EIAV -infected horse.

Reference - Authors: Chiara Nenci; Marie-Luise Zahno; Hans-Rudolf Vogt; Gabriela Obexer-Ruff; Marcus G Doherr; Reto Zanoni; Ernst Peterhans; Giuseppe Bertoni
Reference - Title: Vaccination with a T-cell-priming Gag peptide of caprine arthritis encephalitis virus enhances virus replication transiently in vivo.
Epitope - Epitope Comments: Sequence of the epitope can be found in Fluri et. al., Vaccine 24, 597–606 (2006).
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 100 ug, administered at intervals of 21 days.
Assay - Comments: The epitope protects goats from CAEV challenge as measured by decreased viral load.
Assay Antigen - Name: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork (Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus (STRAIN CORK))
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork

Reference - Authors: Chiara Nenci; Marie-Luise Zahno; Hans-Rudolf Vogt; Gabriela Obexer-Ruff; Marcus G Doherr; Reto Zanoni; Ernst Peterhans; Giuseppe Bertoni
Reference - Title: Vaccination with a T-cell-priming Gag peptide of caprine arthritis encephalitis virus enhances virus replication transiently in vivo.
Epitope - Epitope Comments: Sequence of the epitope can be found in Fluri et. al., Vaccine 24, 597–606 (2006).
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 100 ug, administered at intervals of 21 days.
Assay - Comments: At 55 days post-infection, the proviral load in PBMCs of vaccinated goats correlated strongly with IFN-g and IL-4 mRNA expression by PBMCs stimulated with whole-virus preparation.  The authors concluded that the inefficient control of CAEV replication in vaccinated goats did not depend on either IFN-g or IL-4.
Assay Antigen - Name: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork (Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus (STRAIN CORK))
Assay Antigen - Source Organism: Caprine arthritis encephalitis virus strain Cork

Reference - Authors: Chiara Nenci; Marie-Luise Zahno; Hans-Rudolf Vogt; Gabriela Obexer-Ruff; Marcus G Doherr; Reto Zanoni; Ernst Peterhans; Giuseppe Bertoni
Reference - Title: Vaccination with a T-cell-priming Gag peptide of caprine arthritis encephalitis virus enhances virus replication transiently in vivo.
Epitope - Epitope Comments: Sequence of the epitope can be found in Fluri et. al., Vaccine 24, 597–606 (2006).
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 100 ug, administered at intervals of 21 days.
Assay - Comments: At 55 days post-infection, a significant correlation between the proviral load and GM-CSF, and between GM-CSF and either IFN-g or IL-4 mRNA,  was observed in vaccinated goats following PBMC stimulation with either the peptide or whole virus.  The authors suggested that CM-CSF is a key cytokine driving virus replication in the early phase of infection.

Reference - Authors: Tara L Tagmyer; Jodi K Craigo; Sheila J Cook; Deborah L Even; Charles J Issel; Ronald C Montelaro
Reference - Title: Envelope determinants of equine infectious anemia virus vaccine protection and the effects of sequence variation on immune recognition.
1st immunogen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)
Immunization - Comments: At 7 months post-vaccination, ponies were challenged with 10^3 median tissue culture infectious doses of EV0, EV6, or EV13. The EV0 Env gp90 is homologous to that in the EIAVD9 vaccine strain; the EV6 and EV13 gp90 protein sequences differ from EV0 by 6% and 13%, respectively. PBMC were obtained from the ponies on the day of challenge.
Assay - Comments: The stimulation index of the protected group of ponies (n = 14) was significantly higher than that of the group (n = 7) progressing to disease. One of 7 of the group progressing to disease responded versus 8 of 14 of the protected group. It was not determined if the epitope contains both CTL and T helper epitopes or if the observed proliferation response was due to CTL expansion.

Immunization - Comments: At 7 months post-vaccination, ponies were challenged with 10^3 median tissue culture infectious doses of EV0, EV6, or EV13. The EV0 Env gp90 is homologous to that in the EIAVD9 vaccine strain; the EV6 and EV13 gp90 protein sequences differ from EV0 by 6% and 13%, respectively. PBMC were obtained from the ponies on the day of challenge.
Assay - Comments: There was no significant difference in the stimulation index between the protected group of ponies (n = 14) versus the group (n = 7) progressing to disease.

1st immunogen - Name: Equine infectious anemia virus (equine infectious anemia virus EIAV)
Immunization - Comments: At 7 months post-vaccination, ponies were challenged with 10^3 median tissue culture infectious doses of EV0, EV6, or EV13. The EV0 Env gp90 is homologous to that in the EIAVD9 vaccine strain; the EV6 and EV13 gp90 protein sequences differ from EV0 by 6% and 13%, respectively. PBMC were obtained from the ponies on the day of challenge.
Assay - Comments: The cytolytic activity of the protected group of ponies (n = 7) was higher than that of the group (n = 5) progressing to disease, but the difference was not significant.

Reference - Authors: J N Flynn; C A Cannon; J A Beatty; M Mackett; M A Rigby; J C Neil; C Jarrett
Reference - Title: Induction of feline immunodeficiency virus-specific cytotoxic T cells in vivo with carrier-free synthetic peptide.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 50ug peptide 1, followed by 2 doses of 100ug of same antigen administered at intervals of 3 weeks.
Immunization - Comments: Cats were immunized with 50ug of peptide on two occasions, followed by a further two immunizations of 100ug in with 50ug Quil A in 1ml of sterile saline.
Assay - Comments: PBMCs from cats immunized with peptide 1, which consists of a synthetic conjugate of gag (196-208) and env (395-398), failed to proliferate in response to the constituent 10-mer peptide 2.

Reference - Authors: J N Flynn; C A Cannon; J A Beatty; M Mackett; M A Rigby; J C Neil; C Jarrett
Reference - Title: Induction of feline immunodeficiency virus-specific cytotoxic T cells in vivo with carrier-free synthetic peptide.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 50ug peptide 1, followed by 2 doses of 100ug of same antigen administered at intervals of 3 weeks.
Immunization - Comments: Cats were immunized with 50ug of peptide on two occasions, followed by a further two immunizations of 100ug in with 50ug Quil A in 1ml of sterile saline.
Assay - Comments: Fresh PBMCs from cats immunized with peptide 1, which consists of a synthetic conjugate of gag (196-208) and env (395-398), recognized and lysed targets pulsed with the constituent 10-mer peptide 2. In vitro restimulation with the epitope increased the level of specific lysis.
MHC Restriction - Evidence Code: T cell assay -T cell subset identification

Reference - Authors: Adrienne V Li; James J Moon; Wuhbet Abraham; Heikyung Suh; Jamal Elkhader; Michael A Seidman; Minmin Yen; Eung-Jun Im; Maria H Foley; Dan H Barouch; Darrell J Irvine
Reference - Title: Generation of effector memory T cell-based mucosal and systemic immunity with pulmonary nanoparticle vaccination.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 10 ug AL11 on days 0 and 28
Immunization - Comments: Mice were immunized with interbilayer-crosslinked multilamellar vesicles (ICMVs) coated with the epitope.  MPLA and poly I:C were used as adjuvants.
Assay - Comments: Cells from blood and lungs showed a positive response.  Mice immunized with ICMVs showed a stronger response than mice immunized with the soluble peptide alone.

Reference - Authors: Adrienne V Li; James J Moon; Wuhbet Abraham; Heikyung Suh; Jamal Elkhader; Michael A Seidman; Minmin Yen; Eung-Jun Im; Maria H Foley; Dan H Barouch; Darrell J Irvine
Reference - Title: Generation of effector memory T cell-based mucosal and systemic immunity with pulmonary nanoparticle vaccination.
1st immunogen - Dose Schedule: 2 doses of 10 ug AL11 on days 0 and 28
Immunization - Comments: Mice were immunized with interbilayer-crosslinked multilamellar vesicles (ICMVs) coated with the epitope.  MPLA and poly I:C were used as adjuvants.
Assay - Comments: The epitope protected mice from SIV gag-expressing vaccinia virus infection.

Reference - Authors: Daisuke Morita; Yukie Yamamoto; Tatsuaki Mizutani; Takeshi Ishikawa; Juri Suzuki; Tatsuhiko Igarashi; Naoki Mori; Takashi Shiina; Hidetoshi Inoko; Hiroaki Fujita; Kazuhiro Iwai; Yoshimasa Tanaka; Bunzo Mikami; Masahiko Sugita
Reference - Title: Crystal structure of the N-myristoylated lipopeptide-bound MHC class I complex.
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the T Cell clone 2N5.1 was previously described in the cited reference: Morita et al. (2011) J Immunol 187: 608-612 [PMID: 21653836]. PBMCs, obtained from rhesus macaque monkeys, were cultured with the epitope, and antigenic stimulation was repeated every 2 wk in the presence of irradiated autologous PBMCs and IL-2.
Assay - Comments: The monkey kidney epithelial cell line LLC-MK2, transfected with Mamu-B*098, stimulated 2N5.1 cells to produce interferon-γ (IFN-γ) in the presence of the epitope C14nef5. LLC-MK2 cells transfected with other Mamu class I MHC alleles did not present the epitope and stimulate IFN-γ production. Plate-bound Mamu-B*098 was also able to present epitope and stimulate IFN-γ production. Authors refer to the MHC molecule as Mamu-B*098. This may mean  Mamu-B*098:01:01, Mamu-B*098:01:02, Mamu-B*098:02, Mamu-B*098:03, or Mamu-B*098:04.

Reference - Authors: Daisuke Morita; Yukie Yamamoto; Tatsuaki Mizutani; Takeshi Ishikawa; Juri Suzuki; Tatsuhiko Igarashi; Naoki Mori; Takashi Shiina; Hidetoshi Inoko; Hiroaki Fujita; Kazuhiro Iwai; Yoshimasa Tanaka; Bunzo Mikami; Masahiko Sugita
Reference - Title: Crystal structure of the N-myristoylated lipopeptide-bound MHC class I complex.
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the T Cell clone 2N5.1 was previously described in the cited reference: Morita et al. (2011) J Immunol 187: 608-612 [PMID: 21653836]. PBMCs, obtained from rhesus macaque monkeys, were cultured with the epitope, and antigenic stimulation was repeated every 2 wk in the presence of irradiated autologous PBMCs and IL-2. The 2N5.1 TCR was clones and expressed.
Assay - Comments: The affinity of the epitope-specific 2N5.1 TCR for the epitope-Mamu-B*098 complex was determined by surface plasmon resonance. Authors refer to the MHC molecule as Mamu-B*098. This may mean  Mamu-B*098:01:01, Mamu-B*098:01:02, Mamu-B*098:02, Mamu-B*098:03, or Mamu-B*098:04.

Reference - Title: Identifying common T cell responses to major pathogens in rhesus macaques

Reference - Authors: Yukie Yamamoto; Daisuke Morita; Yoko Shima; Akihiro Midorikawa; Tatsuaki Mizutani; Juri Suzuki; Naoki Mori; Takashi Shiina; Hidetoshi Inoko; Yoshimasa Tanaka; Bunzo Mikami; Masahiko Sugita
Reference - Title: Identification and Structure of an MHC Class I-Encoded Protein with the Potential to Present -Myristoylated 4-mer Peptides to T Cells.
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the T cell clone SN45 was previously described in the cited reference: Morita et al. (2013) J Virol 87: 482-488 [PMID: 23097434]. The C14-Gly-Gly-Ala-Ile-Ser (C14nef5)-specific T cell line, SN45, was obtained  from a SIV-infected monkey (MM521). Peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) were cultured with C14-Gly-Gly-Ala-Ile-Ser (C14nef5) and antigenic stimulation was repeated every 2 weeks in the presence of irradiated autologous PBMCs. The SN45-derived TCR α and β cDNAs were cloned and transfected into TCRβ-deficient J.RT3 cells.
Assay - Comments: The J.RT3/SN45 TCR cell line produced IL-2 in response to the epitope presented by HeLa cells transfected with Mamu-B*05104. HeLa cells transfected with Mamu-B*06004 or Mamu-B11L*01 were not stimulatory. The J.RT3/SN45 TCR cell line did not produce IL-2 in response to HeLa-Mamu-B*05104 cells pulsed with the analog C14-GGGI.

Reference - Authors: Yukie Yamamoto; Daisuke Morita; Yoko Shima; Akihiro Midorikawa; Tatsuaki Mizutani; Juri Suzuki; Naoki Mori; Takashi Shiina; Hidetoshi Inoko; Yoshimasa Tanaka; Bunzo Mikami; Masahiko Sugita
Reference - Title: Identification and Structure of an MHC Class I-Encoded Protein with the Potential to Present -Myristoylated 4-mer Peptides to T Cells.
Immunization - Comments: Generation of the T cell clone SN45 was previously described in the cited reference: Morita et al. (2013) J Virol 87: 482-488 [PMID: 23097434]. The SN45-derived TCR α and β cDNAs were cloned and transfected into TCRβ-deficient J.RT3 cells.
Assay - Comments: The SN45 TCR tetramer bound to K562 cells transfected with Mamu-B*05104 and pulsed with the epitope. The SN45 TCR tetramer did not react with K562 cells transfected with Mamu-B*05104 and pulsed with the analog C14-GGGI.

Reference - Authors: Hiroshi Ishii; Saori Matsuoka; Noriko Ikeda; Kyoko Kurihara; Takamasa Ueno; Masafumi Takiguchi; Taeko K Naruse; Akinori Kimura; Masaru Yokoyama; Hironori Sato; Tetsuro Matano
Reference - Title: Determination of a T cell receptor of potent CD8<sup>+</sup> T cells against simian immunodeficiency virus infection in Burmese rhesus macaques.
Immunization - Comments: Epitope-specific CD8+ T-cells were derived from infected Manu-A1*065:01 positive animals. cDNAs encoding TCR variable region (V-J) were amplified. TG40 cells were then infected with the recombinant retroviruses to obtain cells expressing the epitope-specific TCR.
Assay - Comments: Epitope-specific TCR transfected CD8+ cells were tested.

Reference - Authors: Hiroshi Ishii; Saori Matsuoka; Noriko Ikeda; Kyoko Kurihara; Takamasa Ueno; Masafumi Takiguchi; Taeko K Naruse; Akinori Kimura; Masaru Yokoyama; Hironori Sato; Tetsuro Matano
Reference - Title: Determination of a T cell receptor of potent CD8<sup>+</sup> T cells against simian immunodeficiency virus infection in Burmese rhesus macaques.

Reference - Title: Determination of a T cell receptor of potent CD8<sup>+</sup> T cells against simian immunodeficiency virus infection in Burmese rhesus macaques.
Immunization - Comments: Wild type peptide-specific CD8+ T-cells were derived from infected Manu-A1*065:01 positive animals. cDNAs encoding TCR variable region (V-J) were amplified. TG40 cells were then infected with the recombinant retroviruses to obtain cells expressing the wild type peptide-specific TCR.
Assay - Comments: Wild-type peptide-specific TCR transfected CD8+ cells were tested.

Reference - Authors: Kelly D Moynihan; Rebecca L Holden; Naveen K Mehta; Chensu Wang; Mark R Karver; Jens Dinter; Simon Liang; Wuhbet Abraham; Mariane B Melo; Angela Q Zhang; Na Li; Sylvie Le Gall; Bradley L Pentelute; Darrell J Irvine
Reference - Title: Enhancement of Peptide Vaccine Immunogenicity by Increasing Lymphatic Drainage and Boosting Serum Stability.
Immunization - Comments: Animals were immunized with the free epitope, or with the epitope conjugated to a DSPE phospholipid tail through a poly(ethylene glycol) spacer (DSPE-PEG-AL11).
Assay - Comments: Cytokine production was significantly higher after immunization with DSPE-PEG-AL11 compared to the free epitope.

Reference - Authors: Christine D Palmer; Amy R Rappaport; Matthew J Davis; Meghan G Hart; Ciaran D Scallan; Sue-Jean Hong; Leonid Gitlin; Lauren D Kraemer; Sonia Kounlavouth; Aaron Yang; Lindsey Smith; Desiree Schenk; Mojca Skoberne; Kiara Taquechel; Martina Marrali; Jason R Jaroslavsky; Charmaine N Nganje; Elizabeth Maloney; Rita Zhou; Daniel Navarro-Gomez; Adrienne C Greene; Gijsbert Grotenbreg; Renee Greer; Wade Blair; Minh Duc Cao; Shawn Chan; Kyounghwa Bae; Alexander I Spira; Sameek Roychowdhury; David P Carbone; Brian S Henick; Charles G Drake; Benjamin J Solomon; Daniel H Ahn; Amit Mahipal; Steve B Maron; Benny Johnson; Raphael Rousseau; Roman Yelensky; Chih-Yi Liao; Daniel V T Catenacci; Andrew Allen; Andrew R Ferguson; Karin Jooss
Reference - Title: Individualized, heterologous chimpanzee adenovirus and self-amplifying mRNA neoantigen vaccine for advanced metastatic solid tumors: phase 1 trial interim results.
Immunization - Comments: A model antigen cassette containing six NHP-specific MAMU-A*01-restricted SIV viral epitopes (SIV Gag CM9, SIV Env TL9, SIV Env CL9, SIV Tat TL8, SIV Gag LW9 and SIV Pol SV9) was designed. Each minimal epitope, including the epitope, is embedded in a 25 amino acid sequence with 8 amino acids flanking each minimal epitope sequence and inserted into the ChAd68 and samRNA vaccine platforms. The cassette also contains class II helper epitopes. MAMU-A*01-positive rhesus macaques were immunized intramuscularly (i.m.) with 10^12 VP ChAd68 prime, followed by i.m. 300 µg samRNA boosts at 4, 12 and 20 weeks, with or without concomitant administration of s.c. anti-CTLA-4 antibody ipilimumab.
Assay - Comments: Immunization with the ChAd68 vaccine platform induced immune responses against all six antigens, including the epitope at week 4 +/- ipilimumab. Primed T cell responses were boosted following administration of samRNA, with T cell responses still detectable 32 weeks after prime in both groups.
